        "name": "Airport API (Laravel)",
        "description": "Full CRUD API for managing airport planes.\n\n## Framework\nLaravel — routes defined in `routes/web.php` under `/api` prefix.\n\n## Data Model: Plane\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| id | integer | auto | Unique identifier (auto-generated) |\n| model | string | yes | Aircraft model name |\n| airline | string | yes | Airline company name |\n\n## Status Codes\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `200` | OK — request successful |\n| `201` | Created — resource created |\n| `400` | Bad Request — empty/invalid JSON or missing fields |\n| `404` | Not Found — resource does not exist |\n| `500` | Internal Server Error — unexpected error |\n\n## Seed Data (in-memory)\nThe controller starts with 4 pre-loaded planes:\n| ID | Model | Airline |\n|----|-------|---------|\n| 1 | Boeing 747 | Ukraine International |\n| 2 | Airbus A320 | Wizz Air |\n| 3 | Antonov 225 | Antonov Dream Airlines |\n| 4 | Antonov 124 | Antonov Dream Airlines |\n\n⚠️ Data is stored in-memory (`private array $planes`) — all changes reset on server restart. No database integration in current implementation.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
