                        "description": "Creates a new plane record.\n\n**Route:** `POST /api/planes` → `PlaneController@create`\n\nLaravel parses the JSON body automatically via `$request->json()->all()`.\nThe `id` is auto-generated as `count($planes) + 1`.\n\n---\n\n### 📥 Request Body\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| model | string | ✅ yes | Aircraft model name |\n| airline | string | ✅ yes | Airline company name |\n\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"Boeing 737-800\",\n  \"airline\": \"Ryanair\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Response 201 Created\nReturns the newly created plane object.\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": 5,\n  \"model\": \"Boeing 737-800\",\n  \"airline\": \"Ryanair\"\n}\n```\n\n### ❌ Response 400 — Empty or unparseable body\n```json\n{ \"error\": \"Invalid JSON format\" }\n```\n\n### ❌ Response 400 — Missing required fields\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Validation failed\",\n  \"details\": \"Fields \\\"model\\\" and \\\"airline\\\" are required\"\n}\n```\n\n### ❌ Response 500 — Unexpected server error\n```json\n{ \"error\": \"Server error\" }\n```"
