                        "description": "Fully updates all fields of an existing plane. Send both `model` and `airline`.\n\n**Route:** `PUT /api/planes/{id}` → `PlaneController@update`\n\nLaravel accepts this via `Route::match(['put', 'patch'], ...)`. Internally uses `array_merge($plane, $data)` — fields omitted from the request retain their previous values.\n\n---\n\n### 📥 Path Parameter\n| Name | Type | Required | Description |\n|------|------|----------|-------------|\n| id | integer | ✅ yes | ID of the plane to update |\n\n### 📥 Request Body\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| model | string | recommended | New aircraft model |\n| airline | string | recommended | New airline name |\n\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"Boeing 747-800 Updated\",\n  \"airline\": \"Ukraine International\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Response 200 OK\nReturns a message and the merged (updated) plane object.\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Plane 1 updated successfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"model\": \"Boeing 747-800 Updated\",\n    \"airline\": \"Ukraine International\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### ❌ Response 400 — Empty body\n```json\n{ \"error\": \"No data provided\" }\n```\n\n### ❌ Response 404 Not Found\n```json\n{ \"error\": \"Plane not found\" }\n```"
                    },
