                        "description": "Partially updates one or more fields of an existing plane. Only the fields included in the request body will be changed — all others retain their current values.\n\n**Route:** `PATCH /api/planes/{id}` → `PlaneController@update`\n\nHandled by the same controller method as PUT (`Route::match(['put', 'patch'], ...)`).\n\n---\n\n### 📥 Path Parameter\n| Name | Type | Required | Description |\n|------|------|----------|-------------|\n| id | integer | ✅ yes | ID of the plane to update |\n\n### 📥 Request Body (send only fields to change)\n```json\n{ \"airline\": \"Wizz Air\" }\n```\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Response 200 OK\nReturns the merged result — unchanged fields keep their original values.\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Plane 1 updated successfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"model\": \"Boeing 747\",\n    \"airline\": \"Wizz Air\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### ❌ Response 400 — Empty body\n```json\n{ \"error\": \"No data provided\" }\n```\n\n### ❌ Response 404 Not Found\n```json\n{ \"error\": \"Plane not found\" }\n```"
